original: Kilian, Josua, kyrkoherde, Bogla, f. 11/9/96 i Femsjö, Jönköp. 1. G. 23 m. Vivan Fogelberg. — Stud:ex. v. Fjedlstedtska sk. i Upps. 19, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 20, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 23. Tjg. s. v. pastor i Dörby, kommin. i Söraby 23, kyrkoh. i Rogberga sed. 29. Miss:styr. ombud 26-39.
translated: Kilian, Josua, clergyman, born on 11/9/1896 in Femsjö, Jönköping. First marriage to Vivan Fogelberg in 1923. Education: graduated from Fjedlstedtska school in Uppsala in 1919, obtained a degree in theology from Lund University in 1920, completed practical theology examinations and ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1923. Worked as a temporary pastor in Dörby, assistant minister in Söraby in 1923, and became a parish priest in Rogberga since 1929. Represented the Missionary Board as a delegate from 1926 to 1939.
